@node Overview "Overview"

    Handy (Amiga OS3.x M68K) V0.95 R1.02 (26/3/07), ported from
    Handy (Windows         ) V0.95       (19/2/07)
    Handy (Amiga OS4.0 PPC ) V0.80       (22/1/05) and

    AmigaOS3.x M68K port by James Jacobs of Amigan Software in 2007.
    AmigaOS4 port by Mathias "AmiDog" Roslund in 2005.
    Original Windows version by Keith Wilkins in 1998-2007.

Handy is an Atari Lynx emulator. It is quite compatible and most ROMs
should work flawlessly.
  This is a bare-bones implementation. The Amiga elements have been
backported from OS4.0 to OS3.0, also replacing the 0.80 emulation core
with the 0.95 core and adding features. The improvements in this version
(as compared to the OS4.0 version) include:

    * based on 0.95 core, not 0.80 core

    * you can play with a joystick

    * you can use an ASL requester to choose which game to play

    * you can run it from Workbench, including support for ToolTypes

    * You can change games without quitting, by pressing F1

    * you can reset the Lynx by pressing F3

    * support for ZIPped games

    * source code

Perhaps in the future more features from the Windows version will be
added.
  AHI sound is available but is turned off by default for speed (SOUND to
turn it on). Keyboard, joystick (2-button joysticks are best) and CDł˛
joypad (JOYPAD) are supported for input.
  The emulator only runs in its own screen. Most features of the Windows
version are not available.
@endnode

@node Requirements "System Requirements"

@{b}Hardware@{ub}             Required        AGA or CyberGraphX
                                     16Mb of RAM
                                     68040+
                     Recommended     68060+
                                     CDł˛ joypad
@{b}Firmware@{ub}             Required        Kickstart 3.0+
@{b}Software@{ub}             Required        OS3.0+
                     Recommended     AHI
                                     cybergraphics.library

@{b}INCREASE THE STACK@{ub}, 100K (stack 100000 <ENTER>) should be enough

You will need a very fast Amiga to achieve adequate performance. You can
run it either in a 320-pixel wide AGA screen, or in an 8-bitplane (256
colour) CyberGraphX (or Picasso96 emulating CyberGraphX) screen. There is
optional AHI sound.

@{b}SPEED LIMITING OF THE EMULATION IS ONLY DONE IF THE SOUND IS ENABLED!@{ub}

Maybe you could run some patches such as BlazeWCP or FBlit to increase the
speed. These have not been tested with Handy but should help performance.
@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"

@{b}INCREASE THE STACK@{ub}, 100K (stack 100000 <ENTER>) should be enough

@{b}Format:          Handy@{ub}
                 [[FILE=]@{i}romname@{ui}]
                 [REQUESTER]
                 [JOYPAD]
                 [CGFX]
                 [SOUND]
                 [SCREENMODE=@{i}screenmode@{ui}]
                 [NOSTALGIA]

@{b}Template:@{ub}        FILE/A,REQUESTER/S,JOYPAD/S,CGFX/S,SOUND/S,
                          SCREENMODE/N,NOSTALGIA/S

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}         To emulate the Atari Lynx.

@{b}Specification:@{ub}

    FILE/S        : filename of the game (in LNX format) you want to play.

    REQUESTER/S   : use screenmode requester (default: CGFX BestModeID/PAL
                    Lores). Note that this has no effect for AGA-only
                    users.

    JOYPAD/S      : CDł˛ joypad (default: joystick). Joypads and joysticks
                    must be in port '2' (the usual "game" port), not port
                    '1' (the usual "mouse" port).

    CGFX/S        : CGFX instead of direct gfxmem access (default: direct
                    gfxmem access).

    SOUND/S       : AHI sound (default: off).

                    @{b}SPEED LIMITING OF THE EMULATION IS ONLY DONE IF THE
                    SOUND IS ENABLED!@{ub}

    SCREENMODE/N  : use the specified screenmode (default: CGFX
                    BestModeID/PAL Lores). Note that this has no effect
                    for AGA-only users.

    NOSTALGIA/S   : save the screenshot in Nostalgia:samples/ (default:
                    current directory).

    ?             : displays the command line argument format.

The order of the arguments is interchangeable.

You can also use these as ToolTypes.

If you run it from CLI and use the REQUESTER option, the screenmode ID
number (suitable for use as an argument for SCREENMODE) of your chosen
screenmode is displayed afterwards.

The way the screenmode is determined is as follows:

    If CyberGraphX is available,
        If SCREENMODE is specified,
            Use SCREENMODE if suitable, otherwise 320*256*8 AGA PAL mode
        Otherwise, if REQUESTER is specified,
            Use ASL requester to select a screenmode
        Otherwise,
            Choose a suitable CyberGraphX screenmode automagically
    Otherwise,
        Use 320*256*8 AGA PAL mode

Note that the real Atari Lynx takes a second or two to load the game; this
likewise applies to the emulator. If you are unable to run the emulator at
full speed, this delay will obviously be longer. Be patient and the game
will eventually appear :-)
@endnode

@node Controls "Controls"

 * Emulator controls (always available):

  ESC                 - Quit
  F1                  - Load game
  F3                  - Reset
  Help                - Save screenshot (in PCX format)

 * Keyboard keys (always available):

  A or D              - Button A
  S                   - Button B
  Q or E              - Button Opt1
  W                   - Button Opt2
  P or ENTER          - Pause
  Arrow keys          - Left, Right, Up, Down

 * CDł˛ pad buttons (only if JOYPAD is ON):

  Green               - Button Opt1
  Yellow              - Button Opt2
  Red                 - Button A
  Blue                - Button B
  Start               - Pause
  Directional buttons - Left, Right, Up, Down

 * Joystick controls (only if JOYPAD is OFF):

  Firebutton 1        - Button A
  Firebutton 2        - Button B
  Directional buttons - Left, Right, Up, Down

